<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8561&amp;p=89311#p89311"><![CDATA[
No, that's not it.<br />The 3 SPC timers, as the SPC itself, runs at the exact same speed on PAL and NTSC consoles, so does the music engine.<br /><br />It's the game itself which runs based on VBlanks, so it will be 20% slower in PAL, but the music will play at the same speed. Therefore technically it's not the music who finishes too early, it's the game who is too slow, but the result is the same.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Fri Jan 27, 2012 3:56 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
